---
metadata: {
    partial_name: 'Ecommerce | Blocks | Carousel Skeleton'
}
---
{% comment %}
    Hydration skeleton for a product carousel block (New Arrivals / What's Hot).
    Rendered as the first child of .product-carousel.is-loading and overlaid on
    the carousel until <ins-carousel> hydrates (its didLoad event removes the
    .is-loading class). Reuses the .product-card-skeleton styles from the PLP
    filter loader. The html.no-js rules in ecommerce.css restore the raw content if JS is off.
{% endcomment %}
<div class="carousel-skeleton" aria-hidden="true">
    <div class="sk-line sk-heading"></div>
    <div class="spacer xx-large"></div>
    <div class="product-cards grid-x grid-padding-x">
        {% for i in (1..4) %}
        <div class="cell large-3 medium-4 small-12 {% if i > 1 %}hide-for-small-only{% endif %} {% if i > 3 %}hide-for-medium-only{% endif %}">
            <div class="product-card-skeleton">
                <div class="sk-image"></div>
                <div class="sk-line sk-cat"></div>
                <div class="sk-line sk-title"></div>
                <div class="sk-line sk-price"></div>
                <div class="sk-btn"></div>
            </div>
        </div>
        {% endfor %}
    </div>
</div>
{% comment %} Without JS the carousel never hydrates, so the `html.no-js` rules in
    ecommerce.css hide the skeleton and un-clip the raw content. {% endcomment %}
